- Average rating refers to the mean value of user ratings (1-5) for a given content type; 
- Comment count is the total number of comments for each content type; 
- View count represents the total number of views for each content type; 
- The earliest posting author is the first author to post a content of a specific type.

Top-rated refers to the highest average rating from user reviews; 
Rating values range from 1 to 5, with 5 being the highest rating;
The content with the most ratings is considered more reliable if there's a tie in average rating.

; Top-rated content refers to the content with the highest average user rating; 
; Average rating is calculated by summing up all user ratings and dividing by the total number of ratings; 
; Content types may include Web links, Videos, etc.
